(27!)^6 \equiv 1 \pmod{899}
899=30^2 - 1
(p-1)! \equiv -1 \pmod p
28!\equiv-1\pmod{29}\implies 27!(28)\equiv-1
\implies 27!(-1)\equiv-1\implies 27!\equiv1\pmod {29}
\implies (27!)^6\equiv 1\pmod{29}
30!\equiv-1\pmod{31} \implies 27!(28)(29)(30)\equiv-1
\implies 27!(-3)(-2)(-1)\equiv-1\implies 27!(6)\equiv1 \implies 27!(30)\equiv5
5
\implies 27!(-1)\equiv5\implies 27!\equiv-5\pmod{31}
(27!)^6\equiv 5^6\pmod{31}
5^3=125\equiv1\pmod{31} \implies (27!)^3\equiv -1\pmod{31}
\implies (27!)^6\equiv (-1)^2\pmod{31}\equiv1
(31,29)\mid \{(27!)^6-1\}
(31,29)=31\cdot 29=899
